    "content": "<p>3\ufe0f\u20e36\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 36th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a> </p><p>systemd tries to bridge the gap between being modular and flexibily supporting a wide range of systems and devices on one hand, and being somewhat quick and efficient to boot up on the other. These two goals are sometimes opposing forces: on many systems step X has to be done on boot, but each such step X costs dearly on other systems where X is not needed.</p>",
