      "replies_count": 0,
      "reblogs_count": 0,
      "favourites_count": 5,
      "quotes_count": 0,
      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>Oh, and one last note: you might wonder, why this needs to be a stanza of its own, why can&#39;t this just implemented via ConditionPathExists=/sys/module/$module? That&#39;s because that subdir is created when a kmod is begun to be loaded, not when it completed to be loaded. Thus, if we&#39;d use that in modprobe@.service, then the unit could not be used as a synchronization point anymore, as anything ordered After= it, might already be started a time the kmod is still in the process of initialization.</p>",
